# MEMORY — {{AGENT_NAME}}

<!--
  Durable notes the agent keeps about its environment, conventions, lessons.
  Written by the agent (and by you) as the deployment evolves.

  Hermes injects this file into every turn. Keep it under `memory_char_limit`
  (default 3000 chars in config.yaml).

  Good entries:
    - environmental constraints (hardware limits, ports in use, network topology)
    - conventions of this deployment (paths, naming, systemd service name)
    - recurring operational lessons

  Bad entries:
    - transient state (session IDs, recent conversations)
    - duplicates of user profile (that goes in USER.md)
-->
